+# Foundations Lane — Plan
+
+Lane: `foundations`
+
+## Purpose / Big Picture
+
+This lane does not implement game-solving code. It produces the honest baseline artifacts for the Myosu frontier: an authoritative `foundation-plan.md` and a reviewed `review.md` that capture the current state of all lanes, the known execution-layer defects in Fabro/Raspberry, and the path to trustworthy run-truth.
+
+The goal is to establish a reviewed slice of the frontier that other lanes can build on, where "truth" in `execute/status/watch` actually means something — where a "success" report reflects real execution, not a false submit.
+
+## Progress
+
+- [x] (2026-03-20) Inspect repo surfaces: README.md, SPEC.md, PLANS.md, AGENTS.md, specs/031626-00-master-index.md, specs/031826-fabro-primary-executor-decision.md
+- [x] (2026-03-20) Inspect outputs/ directory for existing lane artifacts
+- [x] (2026-03-20) Inspect fabro/programs/ for current program structure
+- [ ] (2026-03-20) Document current frontier state honestly
+- [ ] (2026-03-20) Document known Fabro/Raspberry execution defects
+- [ ] (2026-03-20) Produce `outputs/foundations/foundation-plan.md`
+- [ ] (2026-03-20) Produce `outputs/foundations/review.md`
+
+## Surprises & Discoveries
+
+- Observation: `games:multi-game` lane produced a `review.md` and `spec.md` claiming lane completion, but the task description calls this a "false-submit" — the lane was Raspberry-dispatched but the execution did not produce a truthful success or failure.
+- Observation: No `.raspberry/` state files exist in the worktree, suggesting the Raspberry state path in `fabro/programs/myosu.yaml` (`state_path: ../../.raspberry/myosu-state.json`) has never been written or has been wiped.
+- Observation: The `myosu.yaml` program manifest has 7 units (bootstrap, chain-core, games-traits-implementation, services, product, platform, recurring) but the bootstrap program (`myosu-bootstrap.yaml`) only has 3 units (games, tui, chain). The larger `myosu.yaml` is the aspirational target; `myosu-bootstrap.yaml` is what actually runs.
+- Observation: The `foundations` lane does not appear in any program manifest. It is a meta-lane that produces artifacts about the frontier rather than implementing code.
+
+## Decision Log
+
+- Decision: This lane produces artifacts at `outputs/foundations/`, not at a lane-specific subdirectory under `outputs/<domain>/`.
+  Rationale: "Foundations" is a meta-lane that documents the frontier itself, not a single domain. The artifact location must be accessible to all downstream lanes.
+  Date/Author: 2026-03-20 / foundations lane
+
+## Current Frontier State
+
