+| `games:traits` | TRUSTED — KEEP | 2026-03-19 | `cargo test -p myosu-games` → 10 unit + 4 doctest pass |
+| `tui:shell` | TRUSTED — KEEP | (review.md exists) | `cargo test -p myosu-tui` |
+
+### Untrusted Lanes (bootstrap in progress or stalled)
+
+| Lane | Status | Blocker |
+|------|--------|---------|
+| `chain:runtime` | Restart in progress | Needs honest review completion |
+| `chain:pallet` | Restart in progress | Blocked on `chain:runtime` review |
+| `games:multi-game` | FALSE SUBMIT | Raspberry dispatched execution but truth is untrustworthy |
+
+### Aspirational Lanes (not yet started)
+
+| Lane | Status |
+|------|--------|
+| `games:poker-engine` | Not started |
+| `services:miner` | Not started |
+| `services:validator-oracle` | Not started |
+| `product:play-tui` | Not started |
+| `platform:abstraction` | Not started |
+
+## Known Fabro/Raspberry Defects
+
+### Defect 1: `games:multi-game` False Submit
+
+**Symptom**: The `games:multi-game` lane has a complete `review.md` and `spec.md` claiming the lane is "KEEP" and ready for implementation, but the task description explicitly calls this a "false-submit." The Raspberry dispatch reported success without real execution producing a truthful outcome.
+
+**Impact**: Any lane that depends on `games:multi-game` correctness cannot trust its status. The `execute/status/watch` surface reports a completed lane that did not actually complete.
+
+**Diagnosis**: Unknown. Possible causes:
+- Fabro run completed but with an error that was not propagated to Raspberry state
+- Raspberry state was written but with incorrect status
+- The execution was never actually dispatched
+
+**Required fix**: Rerun `games:multi-game` with a trustworthy proof command and produce a new `review.md` that reflects actual execution results.
+
+### Defect 2: No Raspberry State Files
+
+**Symptom**: The `.raspberry/` directory has no state files. The `myosu.yaml` manifest specifies `state_path: ../../.raspberry/myosu-state.json` but no such file exists.
+
+**Impact**: `raspberry status --manifest fabro/programs/myosu.yaml` cannot read the last known state. The control plane has no durable memory of what has run.
+
+**Diagnosis**: Either the Raspberry CLI has never been run against `myosu.yaml`, or the state path resolution is incorrect relative to the worktree.
+
+**Required fix**: Verify the state path resolution. If the path is wrong, fix the manifest. If the state has never been written, run `raspberry execute` and verify state is persisted.
+
+### Defect 3: Two Program Manifests with Different Scope
+
+**Symptom**: `myosu.yaml` has 7 units; `myosu-bootstrap.yaml` has 3 units. Both reference each other in some lanes but the relationship is unclear.
+
+**Impact**: Contributors may run the wrong manifest or be unclear which is authoritative.
+
+**Diagnosis**: `myosu-bootstrap.yaml` is the narrow bootstrap program (games, tui, chain). `myosu.yaml` is the full program-of-programs. The bootstrap is the current operational entrypoint; the full program is aspirational.
+
+**Required fix**: Document the relationship clearly. The bootstrap manifest should be explicitly labeled as "current operational entrypoint" and the full manifest as "aspirational target."
+
+## Plan of Work
+
+### Step 1: Document Current State Honestly
+
+Produce this `foundation-plan.md` that captures:
+- The exact state of every known lane (trusted, untrusted, aspirational)
+- The three known Fabro/Raspberry defects with diagnosis and required fixes
+- The criteria for trustworthy execution truth
+
+### Step 2: Produce `review.md`
+
+Produce `review.md` with:
+- An honest "KEEP / RESET / REOPEN" judgment for the frontier as a whole
+- A judgment on each individual lane
+- Explicit statement of which lanes are currently trustworthy
+- A list of what must be true before the frontier is trustworthy again
+
+### Step 3: Define Trustworthy Execution Criteria
+
+Codify the following invariant:
+
+> A lane's `execute/status/watch` status is trustworthy iff:
+> 1. The proof command ran to completion (exit 0 or documented expected failure)
+> 2. The Raspberry state was written with the correct status
+> 3. The lane's artifacts (`spec.md`, `review.md`) reflect the actual execution result
+
+### Step 4: Fix `games:multi-game` False Submit
+
+The `games:multi-game` lane must be rerun. Until then, any claim of `games:multi-game` readiness is untrustworthy. The fix is not in the code — it's in the execution layer.
+
+### Step 5: Verify Raspberry State Persistence
+
+Run `raspberry execute --manifest fabro/programs/myosu-bootstrap.yaml` and verify that `state_path` is actually written.
+
+## Validation and Acceptance
+
+This lane is complete when:
+
+1. `outputs/foundations/foundation-plan.md` exists and honestly documents all lanes and known defects
+2. `outputs/foundations/review.md` exists and provides an honest judgment on each lane
+3. The `games:multi-game` false-submit is explicitly called out as untrustworthy
+4. The three defects above are documented with their required fixes
+5. The criteria for "trustworthy execution truth" are explicit and testable
+
+## Idempotence and Recovery
+
+This lane is idempotent. Re-running it will produce the same artifacts unless the underlying frontier state changes. If execution-layer fixes are applied, this lane should be rerun to update the baseline.
+
+## Artifacts
